Jedi Mind Tricks (Vinnie Paz) posted this on their Facebook wall. Laughable:

"
music being leaked doesn't mean you have to FUCKING STEAL IT. Its like dealing with fucking retards. I've worked with the same engineer forever. you think a GROWN ASS MAN would risk his career to put a fucking cd online? and IM the fucking A&R. and NO producer has any mixed songs. just me. retail gets music 7-10 days in advance. XXL and The Source get advance copies for review. everyone is clearly... missing the point: music is going to leak. you don't think after 20 years in the game that we KNOW that? I've sold half a million units ON MY OWN, I don't need amateurs waxing poetic about "how" its happening. not only do these morons STEAL MY SHIT, but they steal it BEFORE the release date and critique it like they're Robert fucking Christgau. when I didn't like shit, I just didn't talk about. one thing I learned over the years: critics are always retards, failed musicians, or sound men. in SOME cases all 3. If you don't like somebody's shit, don't buy it and shut you fucking mouth. If you dig it, support said artist. don't steal someone's livelihood then go online and fucking cry about it like a faggot. and don't tell me its "part of the game". I was part of the game before it was called the "game". I'm gettin on my Jay and Silent Bob shit and going to everyone's crib and punching them dead in the face.
"
